<h1>Forge Digital Protection</h1>
<p class="effective-date">Operational Code of Conduct & Service Terms<br>Effective Date: [Insert Date]</p>

<p>
This document outlines the operational standards, client responsibilities, data handling practices,
and service limitations governing Forge Digital Protection (“Forge,” “Service Provider”)
and all Clients engaging its services.
</p>

<h2>1. Nature of Services</h2>
<p>Forge provides digital risk assessment, security strategy consulting, and guided security implementation support.</p>

<p>Forge operates strictly as an advisory and consulting service.</p>

<ul>
<li>Forge does not access client accounts directly.</li>
<li>Forge does not store client passwords.</li>
<li>Forge does not perform hacking, bypassing, or recovery circumvention.</li>
<li>Forge does not guarantee prevention of compromise.</li>
</ul>

<p>All security changes are performed by the Client under guided instruction.</p>

<h2>2. Professional Conduct Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>Provide accurate information.</li>
<li>Maintain respectful communication.</li>
<li>Refrain from requesting illegal or unethical actions.</li>
<li>Accept the advisory nature of services.</li>
<li>Understand that risk reduction does not equal risk elimination.</li>
</ul>

<p>Forge reserves the right to refuse or terminate service for fraudulent behavior, abusive communication, misrepresentation, or unlawful requests.</p>

<h2>3. No Credential Storage Policy</h2>
<p>Forge does not request, collect, store, or retain passwords, authentication codes, or private access credentials.</p>
<p>Clients retain full control and responsibility over all account access.</p>

<h2>4. Data Handling & Privacy Standards</h2>
<p>Forge may collect the following information for operational purposes:</p>

<ul>
<li>Name</li>
<li>Email address</li>
<li>Business information</li>
<li>Social media handles</li>
<li>Security configuration details voluntarily provided</li>
</ul>

<p>Information is used solely for service delivery, risk assessment, and communication.</p>
<p>Forge does not sell, rent, or trade client information.</p>

<h2>5. Payment & Refund Policy</h2>
<p>All fees are due prior to service activation.</p>
<p>Monthly plans renew automatically unless canceled before the next billing cycle.</p>
<p>Payments are non-refundable once service delivery has begun.</p>

<h2>6. No Guarantee & Risk Acknowledgment</h2>
<p>
Client acknowledges that digital platforms inherently carry risk.
Forge implements structured risk mitigation strategies designed to reduce vulnerability exposure;
however, Forge does not guarantee prevention of hacking, data breaches, platform instability,
or account recovery outcomes.
</p>

<h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
<p>
To the fullest extent permitted by law, Service Provider’s total liability shall not exceed
the total fees paid by Client within the thirty (30) days preceding any claim.
</p>

<p>Forge shall not be liable for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Indirect or consequential damages</li>
<li>Loss of revenue</li>
<li>Loss of data</li>
<li>Platform suspensions or bans</li>
<li>Third-party service failures</li>
</ul>

<h2>8. Independent Status</h2>
<p>
Forge operates as an independent consulting service and is not affiliated with any social media platform,
technology provider, or software company.
</p>

<h2>9. Termination</h2>
<p>
Either party may terminate services in writing.
Forge reserves the right to terminate services immediately if Client violates this Code of Conduct.
Fees for services already rendered are non-refundable.
</p>

<h2>10. Acceptance</h2>
<p>
By purchasing services, checking an agreement acknowledgment box, or submitting payment,
Client confirms they have read, understood, and agreed to these terms.
</p>

